# Available Rules

Use these keywords to generate code:

| Keyword | Description | Reference Files |
|---------|-------------|-----------------|
| `@create-task` | Create a new task skeleton | `include/hvt/tasks/fxaaTask.h`, `source/tasks/fxaaTask.cpp` |
| `@test-aov` | Create a unit test to display an AOV buffer | `test/tests/testFramePasses.cpp` |
| `@test-task` | Create a unit test with custom tasks | `test/tests/testFramePasses.cpp` |

## Usage Examples

### Create a new task including its unit test
```
@create-task Sharpen
@create-task Vignette
@create-task ChromaticAberration
```

### Create a unit test to display a specific AOV buffer
```
@test-aov depth
@test-aov primId
@test-aov Neye
```

### Create a unit test to display a post effect
```
@test-task blur
@test-task fxaa
@test-task SSAO
```

## Reference Files

Each rule uses actual codebase files as the source of truth:

| Rule | Primary References |
|------|-------------------|
| `@create-task` | `include/hvt/tasks/fxaaTask.h`, `source/tasks/fxaaTask.cpp`, `include/hvt/resources/shaders/fxaa.glslfx` |
| `@test-aov` | `test/tests/testFramePasses.cpp` |
| `@test-task` | `test/tests/testFramePasses.cpp`, `test/tests/composeTaskHelpers.h` |

## Notes

- `@create-task` will ask for the task name and create header, implementation, shader, and test files, plus update CMakeLists.txt
- `@test-aov` and `@test-task` will ask which file to add the test to before generating code
- Generated tests include a `// Prompt:` comment documenting the original request
- Tests follow the established patterns in the codebase with proper GPU synchronization and image validation
- All rules reference actual source files rather than embedded templates to stay in sync with the codebase
